{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859920586,"sessionID":"ses_286839261ffe5vMhuvJXyxZ1Bh","part":{"id":"prt_d797ed131001lfpzaNVK6EpZfs","messageID":"msg_d797ec4f000112jrS2iOSO79K2","sessionID":"ses_286839261ffe5vMhuvJXyxZ1Bh","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_436d6b8919824a5ca16dd38d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-025/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-025/design.md`, `changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n## T1. AgentMetadata Pydantic Model — Field Definitions\n\n- [ ] 1.1 Define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- [ ] 1.2 Add 2 required fields: `agent_name: str` (no default), `entrypoint: str` (no default)\n- [ ] 1.3 Add 3 validated fields with defaults: `language: str = \"python\"`, `port: int = 8080`, `build_mode: str = \"local\"`\n- [ ] 1.4 Add 4 string-default optional fields: `requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"`, `registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"`, `registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n- [ ] 1.5 Add 13 `None`-default optional fields: `description`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n- [ ] 1.6 Add `Field(...)` descriptions for all 22 fields\n\n**Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata; m = AgentMetadata(agent_name='test', entrypoint='main.py'); print(len(m.model_fields))\"` outputs 22\n\n---\n\n## T2. AgentMetadata — Language Validator\n\n- [ ] 2.1 Implement `@field_validator(\"language\", mode=\"before\")` that normalizes input to lowercase\n- [ ] 2.2 Accept `\"python\"` and `\"java\"` (case-insensitive)\n- [ ] 2.3 Return `\"python\"` as default when input is `None`\n- [ ] 2.4 Raise `ValueError` with message `\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'.\"` for unsupported values\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage -v` all pass\n\n---\n\n## T3. AgentMetadata — Build Mode Validator\n\n- [ ] 3.1 Implement `@field_validator(\"build_mode\", mode=\"before\")` that normalizes input to lowercase\n- [ ] 3.2 Accept `\"local\"` and `\"cloud\"` (case-insensitive)\n- [ ] 3.3 Return `\"local\"` as default when input is `None`\n- [ ] 3.4 Raise `ValueError` with message `\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'.\"` for unsupported values\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode -v` all pass\n\n---\n\n## T4. AgentMetadata — Port Validator\n\n- [ ] 4.1 Implement `@field_validator(\"port\")` (default mode, after type coercion)\n- [ ] 4.2 Accept ports in range `1..65535`\n- [ ] 4.3 Raise `ValueError` with message `\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\"` for out-of-range values\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidatePort -v` all pass\n\n---\n\n## T5. AgentMetadata — Serialization Tests\n\n- [ ] 5.1 Test `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` excludes all `None` fields\n- [ ] 5.2 Test required fields and defaults are present in dumped output\n- [ ] 5.3 Test minimal construction (required fields only) produces correct defaults\n- [ ] 5.4 Test full construction (all fields) preserves all values\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidCreation -v` and `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataModelDump -v` all pass\n\n---\n\n## T6. MetadataOptions Dataclass — Field Definitions\n\n- [ ] 6.1 Define `MetadataOptions` as a `@dataclass` in `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n- [ ] 6.2 Add 14 optional fields with correct defaults:\n  - `agent_name: Optional[str] = None`\n  - `language: Optional[str] = \"python\"`\n  - `entrypoint: Optional[str] = None`\n  - `port: Optional[int] = 8080`\n  - `build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"`\n  - `requirements_file: Optional[str] = None`\n  - `description: Optional[str] = None`\n  - `workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n  - `router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n  - `readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n  - `readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080`\n  - `registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n  - `registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n  - `registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n  - `agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"`\n\n**Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; o = MetadataOptions(); print(len(o.__dataclass_fields__))\"` outputs 15\n\n---\n\n## T7. MetadataOptions — from_options Classmethod\n\n- [ ] 7.1 Implement `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any])` classmethod\n- [ ] 7.2 Define `known_fields` set with all 15 field names\n- [ ] 7.3 Filter input dict to only known fields (silently ignore unknown keys)\n- [ ] 7.4 Return `cls(**filtered)` instance\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptionsFromOptions -v` all pass\n\n---\n\n## T8. MetadataOptions — Default Values Tests\n\n- [ ] 8.1 Test all 15 fields have expected default values when constructed with no arguments\n- [ ] 8.2 Test `from_options({})` returns instance with all defaults\n- [ ] 8.3 Test `from_options` with partial dict sets only specified fields\n- [ ] 8.4 Test `from_options` with unknown keys ignores them\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py -v` all pass\n\n---\n\n## T9. MetadataService — Class Skeleton and Constants\n\n- [ ] 9.1 Define `MetadataService` class in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- [ ] 9.2 Add class constant `METADATA_FILES: List[str] = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]`\n- [ ] 9.3 Add `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)` storing `self.verbose`\n\n**Verification:** `python -c \"from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService; s = MetadataService(verbose=True); print(s.METADATA_FILES, s.verbose)\"` outputs correct values\n\n---\n\n## T10. MetadataService — load_metadata\n\n- [ ] 10.1 Implement `load_metadata(workspace_path: Path) -> Optional[AgentMetadata]`\n- [ ] 10.2 Iterate through `METADATA_FILES` in priority order\n- [ ] 10.3 For first existing file: open, `yaml.safe_load()`, handle `None` result as `{}`, return `AgentMetadata(**data)`\n- [ ] 10.4 Return `None` if no metadata file exists\n- [ ] 10.5 Do not catch `yaml.YAMLError` or `ValidationError` — let them propagate\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestLoadMetadataPrimaryExists -v`, `::TestLoadMetadataFirstFallback -v`, `::TestLoadMetadataSecondFallback -v`, `::TestLoadMetadataNoneExist -v` all pass\n\n---\n\n## T11. MetadataService — save_metadata\n\n- [ ] 11.1 Implement `save_metadata(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n- [ ] 11.2 Always write to `agent_metadata.yaml` (canonical filename)\n- [ ] 11.3 Use `metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)` for data\n- [ ] 11.4 Call `yaml.dump(data, f, default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip -v`, `::TestSaveMetadataExcludeNone -v`, `::TestSaveMetadataFormat -v` all pass\n\n---\n\n## T12. MetadataService — update_metadata\n\n- [ ] 12.1 Implement `update_metadata(workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata`\n- [ ] 12.2 Call `load_metadata()` — if `None`, create default `AgentMetadata` using `updates` for required fields and `workspace_path.name` fallback for `agent_name`\n- [ ] 12.3 Call `existing.model_copy(update=updates)` for immutable merge with re-validation\n- [ ] 12.4 Call `save_metadata()` with merged result\n- [ ] 12.5 Return merged `AgentMetadata` instance\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestUpdateMetadataMerge -v`, `::TestUpdateMetadataCreateNew -v` all pass\n\n---\n\n## T13. MetadataService — validate_workspace\n\n- [ ] 13.1 Implement `validate_workspace(workspace_path: Path) -> bool`\n- [ ] 13.2 Return `self.load_metadata(workspace_path) is not None`\n- [ ] 13.3 Note: This checks metadata file presence only, not filesystem structure\n\n**Verification:** `python -c \"\nfrom pathlib import Path; from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\ns = MetadataService()\nimport tempfile; ws = Path(tempfile.mkdtemp())\n(ws / 'agent_metadata.yaml').write_text('agent_name: t\\nentrypoint: m\\n')\nprint(s.validate_workspace(ws))  # True\n(ws / 'agent_metadata.yaml').unlink()\nprint(s.validate_workspace(ws))  # False\n\"`\n\n---\n\n## T14. MetadataService — _validate_python_workspace\n\n- [ ] 14.1 Implement `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n- [ ] 14.2 Check at least one `*.py` file exists in workspace root via `workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\")`\n- [ ] 14.3 Raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` if no `.py` files\n- [ ] 14.4 Check requirements file exists (use `metadata.requirements_file` or default `\"requirements.txt\"`)\n- [ ] 14.5 Raise `ValueError(f\"Dependency file not found: {req_file}\")` if missing\n\n**Verification:** Manual test with workspace containing/missing `.py` and `requirements.txt` files\n\n---\n\n## T15. MetadataService — _validate_java_workspace\n\n- [ ] 15.1 Implement `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n- [ ] 15.2 Check `pom.xml` exists in workspace root\n- [ ] 15.3 Raise `ValueError(\"pom.xml is required for Java projects\")` if missing\n\n**Verification:** Manual test with workspace containing/missing `pom.xml`\n\n---\n\n## T16. Round-trip Consistency Test\n\n- [ ] 16.1 Create `AgentMetadata` with mix of required, default, and optional fields\n- [ ] 16.2 Save to YAML via `MetadataService.save_metadata()`\n- [ ] 16.3 Load back via `MetadataService.load_metadata()`\n- [ ] 16.4 Verify all non-None field values match original\n\n**Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip -v` passes\n\n---\n\n## T17. Error Handling Verification\n\n- [ ] 17.1 Verify malformed YAML raises `yaml.YAMLError`\n- [ ] 17.2 Verify unsupported language in YAML raises `ValidationError`\n- [ ] 17.3 Verify missing required field raises `ValidationError`\n- [ ] 17.4 Verify port out of range in update raises `ValidationError` and does not modify file\n\n**Verification:** All covered by existing test classes `TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage`, `TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode`, `TestAgentMetadataValidatePort`\n\n---\n\n## T18. Linting and Type Checking\n\n- [ ] 18.1 Run `ruff check` on `metadata_service.py` and `pack_models.py` — no violations\n- [ ] 18.2 Run `mypy` on `metadata_service.py` and `pack_models.py` — no type errors\n\n**Verification:** `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` and `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` both pass\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nT1 (AgentMetadata fields)\n├── T2 (language validator)\n├── T3 (build_mode validator)\n├── T4 (port validator)\n└── T5 (serialization tests)\n\nT6 (MetadataOptions fields)\n└── T7 (from_options)\n    └── T8 (defaults tests)\n\nT9 (MetadataService skeleton)\n├── T10 (load_metadata)\n├── T11 (save_metadata)\n├── T12 (update_metadata)\n├── T13 (validate_workspace)\n├── T14 (_validate_python_workspace)\n└── T15 (_validate_java_workspace)\n\nT10, T11, T12\n└── T16 (round-trip test)\n\nT2, T3, T4, T10, T12\n└── T17 (error handling)\n\nT1-T17\n└── T18 (linting + type check)\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 | T1, T6, T9 | None |\n| G2 | T2, T3, T4 | T1 |\n| G3 | T7 | T6 |\n| G4 | T10, T11, T13, T14, T15 | T9 |\n| G5 | T5, T8 | T2, T3, T4, T7 |\n| G6 | T12 | T10, T11 |\n| G7 | T16, T17 | T10, T11, T12, T2, T3, T4 |\n| G8 | T18 | T1-T17 |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | AgentMetadata has 22 fields with correct types and defaults | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidCreation -v` |\n| AC2 | Language validator accepts python/java, rejects others | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage -v` |\n| AC3 | Build mode validator accepts local/cloud, rejects others | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode -v` |\n| AC4 | Port validator accepts 1-65535, rejects out of range | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataValidatePort -v` |\n| AC5 | model_dump(exclude_none=True) works correctly | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py::TestAgentMetadataModelDump -v` |\n| AC6 | MetadataOptions has 15 fields with correct defaults | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptionsDefaults -v` |\n| AC7 | from_options filters known fields, ignores unknown | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptionsFromOptions -v` |\n| AC8 | load_metadata tries primary → fallback1 → fallback2 → None | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -k LoadMetadata -v` |\n| AC9 | save_metadata writes clean YAML with correct formatting | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -k SaveMetadata -v` |\n| AC10 | update_metadata merges and validates correctly | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -k UpdateMetadata -v` |\n| AC11 | validate_workspace returns boolean based on metadata presence | Manual verification |\n| AC12 | _validate_python_workspace checks .py and requirements file | Manual verification |\n| AC13 | _validate_java_workspace checks pom.xml | Manual verification |\n| AC14 | Round-trip save → load produces equivalent values | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py::TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip -v` |\n| AC15 | All tests pass | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_service.py cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py cmd/cli/tests/models/test_pack_models.py -v` |\n| AC16 | No linting violations | `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` |\n| AC17 | No type errors | `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\">\nERROR [101:24] Arguments missing for parameters \"description\", \"region\", \"version\", \"image\", \"auth\", \"requirements_file\", \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"workload_manager_url\", \"router_url\", \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\", \"agent_id\", \"session_id\", \"k8s_deployment\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/tests/services/test_metadata_model.py\">\nERROR [11:16] Arguments missing for parameters \"description\", \"language\", \"port\", \"build_mode\", \"region\", \"version\", \"image\", \"auth\", \"requirements_file\", \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"workload_manager_url\", \"router_url\